{"word":"Siege","slug":"siege","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Siege</b> Offer of peace must be made to the city before beginning<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=20&verse=12'>Deu 20:12</a><br/> Conducted by erecting embankments parallel to the walls of the besieged city<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=20&verse=20'>Deu 20:20</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=29&verse=3'>Isa 29:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=37&verse=33'>Isa 37:33</a><br/> Battering rams used in<br/> <a href='S:Battering-Ram'>Battering-Ram</a><br/> Distress of the inhabitants during<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=6&verse=29'>2Ki 6:29</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=25&verse=3'>2Ki 25:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=9&verse=20'>Isa 9:20</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=36&verse=12'>Isa 36:12</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=19&verse=9'>Jer 19:9</a><br/> Cannibalism in<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=6&verse=29'>2Ki 6:29</a><br/> Instances of siege:<br/> - Of Jericho<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=6'>Jos 6</a> <br/> - Of Rabbah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=11&verse=1'>2Sa 11:1</a> <br/> - Of Abel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=20&verse=15'>2Sa 20:15</a> <br/> - Of Gibbethon<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=15&verse=27'>1Ki 15:27</a> <br/> - Of Tirzah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=16&verse=17'>1Ki 16:17</a> <br/> - Of Jerusalem:<br/> b by the children of Judah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=1&verse=8'>Jdg 1:8</a><br/> b by David<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=5&verse=6'>2Sa 5:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=5&verse=9'>2Sa 5:9</a><br/> b by Rezin, king of Syria, and Pekah, son of Remaliah, king of Israel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=16&verse=5'>2Ki 16:5</a><br/> b by Nebuchadnezzar<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=24&verse=11'>2Ki 24:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=27&chapter=1&verse=1'>Dan 1:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=25&verse=3'>2Ki 25:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=52'>Jer 52</a><br/> b by Sennacherib<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=32&verse=23'>2Ch 32:23</a><br/> - Of Samaria<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=20&verse=1'>1Ki 20:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=6&verse=24'>2Ki 6:24</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=17&verse=5'>2Ki 17:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=18&verse=11'>2Ki 18:11</a> "}]}